        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 9:23PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 922 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Saranac to 10 miles south of Carson City.
Movement was east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ionia...               St. Johns...           Portland...
Belding...             Lake Odessa...         Saranac...
Carson City...         Elsie...               DeWitt...
Eureka...              Orleans...             Ovid...
Fowler...              Sebewa...              North Star...
Westphalia...          Lyons...               Maple Rapids...
Muir...                Ashley...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
